Q(s,a)

Meaning:

In each state, pick the action with highest Q.

Following those actions gives the optimal path.

Q-Learning does NOT search paths.
It learns values.
Path emerges from values.

6️⃣ What Do Hyperparameters Mean?
ε (epsilon)

Exploration rate.

With probability ε → random action

Otherwise → best known action

Prevents missing better paths.

α (alpha)

Learning rate.

How fast Q-values update.

High α → fast but unstable.

Low α → slow but stable.

γ (gamma)

Discount factor.

How much future rewards matter.

Close to 1 → long-term thinking.

Close to 0 → short-term thinking.

Episodes

Number of times agent runs from start to goal.

More episodes → better learning.

